						<summary>

						<p>On a fragment built into the wall (left of entrance) of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> of the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p>1071 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 993, Virōdhikṛit, Pushya śu. 1, Sunday, Uttarāyaṇa-saṁkrānti, corresponding to 1071 A.D., December 25.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of land to the god Bhōgēśvara, out of a grant made earlier. The record is much damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
